          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " illustrate how tax loopholes, preferences, and shelters allow moguls such as Jeff Bezos and Warren Buffett to pay a lower effective tax rate than everyone else. Eisinger also reviews the",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
